This paper deals with optimization of a sequential decision-making problem with controls, which is a common theme in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the asymptotic optimality of a proposed policy, which is a common topic in the subfield of statistical learning theory (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves optimization of costs and trade-offs, which is a common theme in optimization and operations research (cs.RO). The paper also involves the use of algorithms and computational methods, which are common themes in computer science (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation and evaluation of a proposed policy, which is a common theme in software engineering (cs.SE).
